1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,560
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:03,004
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,824 --> 00:00:07,191
I'll go now.
I need to take the last train.

4
00:00:07,191 --> 00:00:08,476
All right, you should go.

5
00:00:09,089 --> 00:00:10,089
What about you two?

6
00:00:10,089 --> 00:00:12,279
I think I'll need another hour or two.

7
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:15,116
I don't have to worry
about the last train. I've got my scooter.

8
00:00:15,116 --> 00:00:16,149
You should go, Assistant Manager.

9
00:00:16,149 --> 00:00:17,584
Then I'll leave first.

10
00:00:27,776 --> 00:00:28,776
It's done.

11
00:00:37,163 --> 00:00:38,163
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

12
00:00:40,083 --> 00:00:41,976
Let's stop here
and finish the rest tomorrow.

13
00:00:41,976 --> 00:00:43,671
It is tomorrow.

14
00:00:43,671 --> 00:00:45,498
In a few hours,
it'll be time to work again.

15
00:00:45,498 --> 00:00:46,980
Stop and get up.

16
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:48,849
Go home and get even a little sleep.

17
00:00:49,097 --> 00:00:51,990
Team Manager, I'm generally the type...

18
00:00:51,990 --> 00:00:54,365
who can't afford to lose momentum
once I'm working.

19
00:00:55,423 --> 00:00:58,242
Don't tell me
you're planning to sleep here.

20
00:00:58,242 --> 00:01:01,308
I'm actually very sensitive,

21
00:01:01,624 --> 00:01:04,257
so if I sleep somewhere unfamiliar,
I can't sleep at all.

22
00:01:05,983 --> 00:01:07,434
So you're more sensitive than you look.

23
00:01:08,224 --> 00:01:10,838
All right then. I'll head out first.

24
00:01:11,224 --> 00:01:12,840
- Get home safe.
- Yes.

25
00:01:18,711 --> 00:01:21,315
(Kangsu Construction)

26
00:01:56,623 --> 00:01:58,418
What the? What happened?

27
00:02:03,024 --> 00:02:04,387
Team Manager, wake up. Hurry.

28
00:02:04,387 --> 00:02:06,663
What? Why? What time is it?

29
00:02:06,663 --> 00:02:08,428
- It's 8 a.m.
- It's 8 a.m?

30
00:02:09,224 --> 00:02:11,657
What happened? You left before dawn.

31
00:02:11,657 --> 00:02:13,800
I'm generally a compassionate person,

32
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,983
so I came back.

33
00:02:14,983 --> 00:02:16,850
Really? Why didn't I notice?

34
00:02:17,157 --> 00:02:19,540
I was just leaning on the sofa
with my eyes closed for a bit.

35
00:02:21,542 --> 00:02:24,612
(Five hours earlier)

36
00:02:30,457 --> 00:02:31,952
I knew this would happen.

37
00:03:17,097 --> 00:03:20,100
For someone so sensitive,
you were snoring away.

38
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:22,102
I usually don't snore.

39
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:28,357
Hey, Seung Ri.

40
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:29,843
Where are you?

41
00:03:30,342 --> 00:03:33,947
If you're at work,
how about morning coffee at the café?

42
00:03:34,976 --> 00:03:36,790
Café? I'm already upstairs.

43
00:03:36,790 --> 00:03:38,218
Let's just grab coffee in the pantry.

44
00:03:38,524 --> 00:03:39,720
Okay, see you later.

45
00:03:40,876 --> 00:03:42,256
I'll head out first.

46
00:03:42,591 --> 00:03:46,163
And let's keep it a secret
that we worked overnight together.

47
00:03:46,163 --> 00:03:47,595
What? Why?

48
00:03:48,024 --> 00:03:50,731
I told you to be more attentive.
Think about Manager Seo's arrow.

49
00:03:51,056 --> 00:03:52,056
Please.

50
00:03:52,424 --> 00:03:53,424
Wait.

51
00:03:54,083 --> 00:03:57,137
Wipe your eye gunk and drool
in the restroom.

52
00:03:57,610 --> 00:03:59,102
I didn't drool.

53
00:04:02,391 --> 00:04:06,447
But how did I sleep so soundly
without waking up once?

54
00:04:06,557 --> 00:04:07,824
Good morning.

55
00:04:10,376 --> 00:04:11,385
You're all early.

56
00:04:12,052 --> 00:04:14,787
Did you two stay out last night?

57
00:04:14,787 --> 00:04:15,791
What?

58
00:04:16,691 --> 00:04:19,024
Sorry? Stay out?

59
00:04:19,257 --> 00:04:20,728
Why would you think that?

60
00:04:21,824 --> 00:04:22,824
Exactly.

61
00:04:24,157 --> 00:04:27,067
Come to think of it, you're wearing
the same clothes as yesterday.

62
00:04:28,357 --> 00:04:29,757
Good morning.

63
00:04:29,757 --> 00:04:31,991
Team Manager Ko,
why didn't you come home last night?

64
00:04:31,991 --> 00:04:33,239
Did you pull an all-nighter?

65
00:04:36,391 --> 00:04:39,313
Yes, I couldn't go home because of work.

66
00:04:40,991 --> 00:04:42,982
With Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

67
00:04:43,224 --> 00:04:44,251
Sorry?

68
00:04:46,019 --> 00:04:49,223
Yes, I also pulled an all-nighter.
There's a lot of work.

69
00:04:50,616 --> 00:04:52,256
Just the two of you?

70
00:04:53,124 --> 00:04:54,124
Chief Ko.

71
00:04:54,124 --> 00:04:55,624
Are you two really dating?

72
00:04:55,624 --> 00:04:56,997
- No!
- No!

73
00:04:56,997 --> 00:04:59,391
What kind of ridiculous nonsense is that?

74
00:05:00,074 --> 00:05:02,736
Let's stop the chatter. We're at work.

75
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:04,024
Sorry.

76
00:05:04,024 --> 00:05:06,108
All right, everyone. You know...

77
00:05:06,108 --> 00:05:07,608
the competition is scheduled
for next week, right?

78
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:11,912
I've sent all the details like time,
presentation order, judging method...

79
00:05:11,912 --> 00:05:14,624
by email, so check them...

80
00:05:14,624 --> 00:05:16,157
and prepare without any issues.

81
00:05:16,157 --> 00:05:18,218
Let's give it our best again today.

82
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:35,969
Should I get your rice too, Mom?

83
00:05:37,338 --> 00:05:38,839
Are you not even going to talk to me now?

84
00:05:39,476 --> 00:05:41,174
Am I not your daughter anymore
because I quit med school?

85
00:05:43,690 --> 00:05:46,680
Then do you even see me as your mom?

86
00:05:47,791 --> 00:05:49,983
It's not that I don't see you as my mom.

87
00:05:50,237 --> 00:05:52,600
I knew you too well, so I couldn't say it.

88
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,506
Fine, it's your life.

89
00:05:54,506 --> 00:05:56,924
Do whatever you want. What's the problem?

90
00:05:56,924 --> 00:05:59,112
How long are you going to be like this?

91
00:05:59,723 --> 00:06:01,895
I really had no choice.

92
00:06:01,895 --> 00:06:04,056
Fine, do what you want.

93
00:06:04,056 --> 00:06:06,867
I won't interfere in your life anymore.

94
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:24,563
That temper of hers.

95
00:06:27,024 --> 00:06:29,223
I should've just let her eat.

96
00:06:35,424 --> 00:06:37,524
She shouldn't skip meals because of me.

97
00:06:40,262 --> 00:06:41,891
I should've tried harder to comfort her.

98
00:06:46,496 --> 00:06:47,674
Again?

99
00:06:49,517 --> 00:06:51,345
Is something really wrong?

100
00:06:53,657 --> 00:06:55,802
Seo Seung Wu, get a grip.

101
00:06:55,802 --> 00:06:57,384
What are you even saying?

102
00:06:59,024 --> 00:07:01,924
No matter how big a fan you are
of "The ER Witch,"

103
00:07:01,924 --> 00:07:05,392
the author is that crazy girl.

104
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:08,934
Right, forget it.

105
00:07:09,377 --> 00:07:10,893
Just forget it.

106
00:07:18,363 --> 00:07:22,041
What? She didn't come home yesterday?

107
00:07:32,291 --> 00:07:34,821
What happened? Did you stay out?

108
00:07:35,057 --> 00:07:36,112
Sorry, Mom.

109
00:07:36,112 --> 00:07:38,656
There was too much work,
so I stayed overnight at the office.

110
00:07:39,891 --> 00:07:41,828
Are you okay now, Mom?

111
00:07:42,123 --> 00:07:45,365
Does that matter? Come home early today.

112
00:07:56,143 --> 00:08:00,180
Joy, I've been having a hard time lately.

113
00:08:01,643 --> 00:08:05,257
My youngest, Eun Nim,
dropped out of med school.

114
00:08:05,257 --> 00:08:07,191
Yes, I know.

115
00:08:07,191 --> 00:08:10,157
What? You knew too?

116
00:08:13,090 --> 00:08:14,613
What is going on with everyone?

117
00:08:15,376 --> 00:08:18,898
All the important things
are being kept from me.

118
00:08:20,024 --> 00:08:21,320
Am I an outcast in this house?

119
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:25,038
If you feel lonely as an outcast,
shall I be your friend?

120
00:08:26,857 --> 00:08:30,010
You, my friend? How?

121
00:08:30,249 --> 00:08:32,149
I'll be someone you can talk to.

122
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:36,483
What is troubling you the most right now?

123
00:08:38,024 --> 00:08:39,987
Of course it's my children.

124
00:08:41,057 --> 00:08:43,290
Not one of them is turning out
the way I want.

125
00:08:43,491 --> 00:08:46,727
Children cannot live
only within their parents' time.

126
00:08:47,324 --> 00:08:49,963
They have their own lives.

127
00:08:50,357 --> 00:08:53,133
So they're only mine
while they're in my arms?

128
00:08:56,163 --> 00:08:57,670
After raising them all this way...

129
00:08:59,636 --> 00:09:01,707
I ended up coming here again.

130
00:09:02,757 --> 00:09:05,257
It's a place filled
with humiliation and disgrace for me,

131
00:09:05,724 --> 00:09:08,157
but to meet her, I had no choice.

132
00:09:09,057 --> 00:09:10,217
Why did she go on hiatus?

133
00:09:11,157 --> 00:09:13,587
Could something really have happened?

134
00:09:38,111 --> 00:09:40,276
Fine, it's your life.

135
00:09:40,276 --> 00:09:42,549
Do whatever you want. What's the problem?

136
00:09:42,549 --> 00:09:44,785
How long are you going to be like this?

137
00:09:45,391 --> 00:09:47,521
I really had no choice.

138
00:09:47,521 --> 00:09:49,711
Fine, do what you want.

139
00:09:49,711 --> 00:09:52,459
I won't interfere in your life anymore.

140
00:09:54,424 --> 00:09:55,929
I couldn't write again.

141
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,598
(Due to personal circumstances,
this episode has been postponed.)

142
00:09:59,437 --> 00:10:01,201
How do I make Mom understand?

143
00:10:03,524 --> 00:10:05,038
Something must have happened.

144
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:09,030
She looks like she's lost everything.
That's not her usual self.

145
00:10:09,857 --> 00:10:12,079
What could it be?
What could have happened?

146
00:10:13,324 --> 00:10:14,548
A breakup...

147
00:10:16,457 --> 00:10:20,153
Right, the only way is to show her
I've succeeded as a writer.

148
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:27,093
Opportunity knocks.

149
00:10:27,770 --> 00:10:29,796
I have to find out why she went on hiatus.

150
00:10:30,491 --> 00:10:31,798
Like a butterfly, I fly.

151
00:10:36,837 --> 00:10:38,189
("Blood pressure rising to 85!",
Just as expected.)

152
00:10:38,189 --> 00:10:39,640
(The bleeding was practically
under control now.)

153
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:48,849
("Keep suctioning!")

154
00:10:48,849 --> 00:10:50,584
(As the blood was suctioned away,
the spleen was clearly exposed.)

155
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:53,270
Hey.

156
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:58,025
What are you doing in my seat?

157
00:10:59,864 --> 00:11:02,562
I'm sorry, I was just passing by, and...

158
00:11:03,191 --> 00:11:05,365
I was curious why you went on hiatus,

159
00:11:06,091 --> 00:11:08,948
and as I kept reading,
it got so exciting that...

160
00:11:09,424 --> 00:11:11,261
I got carried away. I'm sorry.

161
00:11:11,261 --> 00:11:13,473
You're truly hopeless.

162
00:11:16,357 --> 00:11:17,741
Hopeless?

163
00:11:18,524 --> 00:11:20,957
Isn't that a bit harsh?

164
00:11:22,157 --> 00:11:25,719
Honestly, I don't want anything
to do with you either.

165
00:11:25,989 --> 00:11:29,656
To be blunt, every time I see you,
it's like facing my worst enemy.

166
00:11:30,657 --> 00:11:31,657
And?

167
00:11:32,041 --> 00:11:33,660
I still like "The ER Witch."

168
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:38,056
Whatever. What can I do? I just like it.

169
00:11:39,524 --> 00:11:41,391
Let's collaborate.

170
00:11:41,391 --> 00:11:42,704
You think I'm crazy?

171
00:11:42,704 --> 00:11:45,042
You think I'd entrust my novel
to someone like you?

172
00:11:45,257 --> 00:11:47,774
If you hate me that much,

173
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:50,110
we can just hold meetings online.

174
00:11:50,422 --> 00:11:53,145
We don't have to meet in person.

175
00:11:53,424 --> 00:11:55,716
No, I don't want to.

176
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:59,357
Look. Have you seen my webtoon?

177
00:11:59,357 --> 00:12:00,954
The producer said he sent it to you.

178
00:12:03,091 --> 00:12:06,016
No, I didn't.
It felt like a waste of time.

179
00:12:06,757 --> 00:12:08,128
A waste of time?

180
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:14,263
Should I leave, or will you move?

181
00:12:14,263 --> 00:12:15,263
Of course...

182
00:12:17,124 --> 00:12:19,039
I'll move.
You need to upload your episode.

183
00:12:19,039 --> 00:12:20,039
But,

184
00:12:20,969 --> 00:12:23,403
once you finish your upload,
read my webtoon.

185
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:27,680
We'll talk again then.

186
00:12:32,316 --> 00:12:34,383
No more hiatus from now on.

187
00:13:11,391 --> 00:13:13,093
What is this? I didn't order it.

188
00:13:13,249 --> 00:13:15,628
He ordered it for you.

189
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:20,132
Seriously.

190
00:13:20,976 --> 00:13:22,802
He also asked me to pass this along.

191
00:13:23,157 --> 00:13:24,157
Sorry?

192
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:29,309
(At 87, 88... Rising!)

193
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:31,645
(Suction!)

194
00:13:41,776 --> 00:13:44,557
(Here's the webtoon
"Secretary by Nature.")

195
00:13:51,624 --> 00:13:54,733
So, have you thought about my offer?

196
00:13:58,603 --> 00:14:00,840
Can't you change your mind?

197
00:14:01,724 --> 00:14:03,577
You can really make use of your skills,

198
00:14:04,191 --> 00:14:06,746
and you'll be paid accordingly.

199
00:14:07,303 --> 00:14:09,382
Why are you being so stubborn?

200
00:14:10,699 --> 00:14:13,386
What? Should I raise the salary?

201
00:14:14,691 --> 00:14:17,057
Ko Dae Chi, do you think...

202
00:14:17,517 --> 00:14:19,358
I'm doing this just to get more money?

203
00:14:20,257 --> 00:14:22,824
Then what's the problem?

204
00:14:22,824 --> 00:14:23,830
Hey, Seong Jun.

205
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:28,191
Think of our loyalty, our old ties.

206
00:14:28,191 --> 00:14:30,570
Loyalty? Old ties?

207
00:14:32,491 --> 00:14:34,274
Do we still have anything like that?

208
00:14:34,424 --> 00:14:37,343
Fine, forget all that.

209
00:14:37,876 --> 00:14:40,713
Then are you doing that well?

210
00:14:41,509 --> 00:14:44,176
If so, why are you still cleaning
at this company?

211
00:14:44,176 --> 00:14:46,786
With your pride,
you should've quit long ago.

212
00:14:48,324 --> 00:14:49,856
You're right.

213
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:54,847
Even if I want to quit,
my situation won't allow it.

214
00:14:56,082 --> 00:14:58,731
Then why keep refusing?

215
00:15:00,883 --> 00:15:02,435
Anyway, decide within a week.

216
00:15:02,916 --> 00:15:05,137
I can't leave that position vacant
for long, got it?

217
00:15:13,263 --> 00:15:15,381
I'm going nuts. What is this?

218
00:15:15,823 --> 00:15:17,583
Did I get through to him or not?

219
00:15:18,210 --> 00:15:20,620
I can't tell at all
since he shows no expression.

220
00:15:26,023 --> 00:15:28,923
Where are you?
If you have time, let's talk.

221
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:36,603
Dae Chi offered you
the executive assistant position, right?

222
00:15:36,604 --> 00:15:37,636
What will you do?

223
00:15:39,016 --> 00:15:41,474
Actually, there are some issues at home.

224
00:15:41,896 --> 00:15:45,111
I still haven't told my wife
that I lost my job.

225
00:15:45,283 --> 00:15:46,579
I can't hide it anymore.

226
00:15:47,744 --> 00:15:49,110
That must've been really hard on you.

227
00:15:49,982 --> 00:15:51,849
Considering my situation,

228
00:15:51,849 --> 00:15:54,462
it's not easy to refuse Dae Chi's offer.

229
00:15:54,462 --> 00:15:58,136
But my heart just won't let me accept it.

230
00:15:58,136 --> 00:15:59,505
Just take it.

231
00:16:00,096 --> 00:16:01,563
I did, so why can't you?

232
00:16:02,676 --> 00:16:05,165
Like you said,
we're the heads of our families.

233
00:16:07,623 --> 00:16:10,368
Maybe I haven't been desperate enough yet.

234
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:15,975
That's strange.

235
00:16:16,170 --> 00:16:19,345
Why is there only one earring?
Where did it go?

236
00:16:20,491 --> 00:16:22,983
I've been wearing them every day.

237
00:16:23,691 --> 00:16:25,018
Where did it go?

238
00:16:26,889 --> 00:16:29,123
This is frustrating.
Where did it disappear to?

239
00:16:30,288 --> 00:16:32,063
Maid!

240
00:16:32,063 --> 00:16:33,191
Yes, Madam.

241
00:16:33,191 --> 00:16:35,128
Have you seen my other earring?

242
00:16:35,128 --> 00:16:36,629
No, I haven't.

243
00:16:37,097 --> 00:16:39,499
Where on earth did it fall off?

244
00:16:41,691 --> 00:16:43,003
When did you get here, Jeong Ran?

245
00:16:43,003 --> 00:16:45,271
Hello. About an hour ago.

246
00:16:45,991 --> 00:16:46,991
How does it taste?

247
00:16:48,690 --> 00:16:52,044
Perfect. How did you get it just right
by eyeballing the ingredients?

248
00:16:52,636 --> 00:16:55,091
Mother, you should pass down
your cooking skills...

249
00:16:55,091 --> 00:16:57,290
to me, your daughter-in-law.

250
00:16:57,290 --> 00:17:00,023
If you want to learn,
go change your clothes first.

251
00:17:00,791 --> 00:17:03,623
What's wrong with what I'm wearing?
I just need an apron.

252
00:17:04,002 --> 00:17:05,958
An apron... Here it is.

253
00:17:10,736 --> 00:17:14,433
Are you making fresh kimchi?
The color looks amazing.

254
00:17:14,824 --> 00:17:16,369
Try some.

255
00:17:20,129 --> 00:17:21,849
It's delicious. The best.

256
00:17:21,849 --> 00:17:22,849
Right?

257
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:26,946
Looking at you two,

258
00:17:27,316 --> 00:17:29,649
you seem like
a close mother-in-law and daughter-in-law.

259
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:31,049
Mr. Ju.

260
00:17:31,717 --> 00:17:34,383
Why do you keep saying things
that make me uncomfortable?

261
00:17:35,623 --> 00:17:37,556
You were here.

262
00:17:38,003 --> 00:17:39,825
You're so subtle, I didn't notice.

263
00:17:42,263 --> 00:17:44,163
That man, seriously.

264
00:17:45,243 --> 00:17:47,633
Mother, I want to learn too.

265
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:58,945
Mother, I'll take this vase.

266
00:17:59,423 --> 00:18:00,513
Stop.

267
00:18:01,156 --> 00:18:03,115
He just fell asleep. Go on out.

268
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,617
Okay...

269
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:59,490
It's me, Mr. Seo.

270
00:19:00,690 --> 00:19:02,823
Stop by my house before you leave work.

271
00:19:05,056 --> 00:19:06,056
All right.

272
00:19:12,656 --> 00:19:15,623
Manager Seo, please taste this.

273
00:19:17,523 --> 00:19:19,725
It's for the after-party menu
on competition day.

274
00:19:19,725 --> 00:19:22,928
I picked a few options, but...

275
00:19:27,529 --> 00:19:30,936
Seems like you prepared it out of concern
for my lunch, but I'll pass.

276
00:19:31,790 --> 00:19:33,872
I figured.

277
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:36,575
To talk to you, I should bring up work.

278
00:19:36,575 --> 00:19:37,809
My mistake.

279
00:19:38,856 --> 00:19:42,556
Did you check the basic design
Lucas sent this morning?

280
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:43,623
What do you think?

281
00:19:43,623 --> 00:19:46,952
Sorry? I'll check it right away.

282
00:19:48,256 --> 00:19:49,256
Seo Seung Ri.

283
00:19:51,856 --> 00:19:54,426
Gyeol and Ms. Cho Eun Ae like each other.

284
00:19:56,623 --> 00:19:59,037
It seems like...

285
00:19:59,037 --> 00:20:00,984
they don't seem to realize it yet.

286
00:20:04,283 --> 00:20:05,871
What exactly are you trying to say?

287
00:20:06,869 --> 00:20:09,742
Let's make sure we win.
Our team versus theirs.

288
00:20:12,078 --> 00:20:15,615
You've rarely lost to anyone in your life,
right?

289
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:18,190
Win this competition...

290
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:20,656
and show those two,
who're giving you a hard time,

291
00:20:20,656 --> 00:20:23,055
what you're really capable of, okay?

292
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:33,490
What is all this?

293
00:20:34,256 --> 00:20:35,256
You can take it.

294
00:20:36,649 --> 00:20:38,749
But where's the Team Manager
and Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

295
00:20:39,643 --> 00:20:42,090
Ms. Cho said
she'd stop by somewhere first,

296
00:20:42,090 --> 00:20:43,475
and the Team Manager is on a call.

297
00:20:44,676 --> 00:20:47,980
Are those two hiding somewhere,
being all lovey-dovey?

298
00:20:49,723 --> 00:20:51,350
I'm going to get some fresh air.

299
00:20:54,990 --> 00:20:57,190
What's wrong with her these days?

300
00:20:58,902 --> 00:21:01,193
The pain of betrayal is always the worst.

301
00:21:03,329 --> 00:21:05,797
I can't believe I'm feeling
a sense of camaraderie with her.

302
00:21:12,556 --> 00:21:14,173
You're out here, Manager Seo?

303
00:21:17,270 --> 00:21:19,003
What's wrong?

304
00:21:19,876 --> 00:21:22,414
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, let's talk for a moment.

305
00:21:22,916 --> 00:21:24,383
Okay.

306
00:21:35,090 --> 00:21:37,961
What I'm about to say
isn't out of personal feelings...

307
00:21:37,961 --> 00:21:39,598
or any other intention,

308
00:21:39,850 --> 00:21:43,001
but as your supervisor,
so don't misunderstand.

309
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:45,938
Yes, go ahead.

310
00:21:47,406 --> 00:21:49,841
(Not-So-Noble Ko Gyeol)

311
00:21:55,776 --> 00:21:58,150
Don't tell me that's how you saved
the Team Manager's contact.

312
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,418
Well...

313
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:03,390
I've been watching you for a while,

314
00:22:03,390 --> 00:22:06,391
and it seems like you lack
the basics of workplace etiquette.

315
00:22:06,956 --> 00:22:09,261
Who saves their superior's number
like that?

316
00:22:10,090 --> 00:22:12,323
That was back when I didn't know him well.

317
00:22:12,583 --> 00:22:14,433
There was some misunderstanding
between us.

318
00:22:14,723 --> 00:22:16,034
I'll fix it right away.

319
00:22:16,206 --> 00:22:18,716
You know there are rumors going around...

320
00:22:18,716 --> 00:22:20,972
about the two of you
in the division, right?

321
00:22:21,309 --> 00:22:23,242
Rumors?

322
00:22:29,409 --> 00:22:30,916
Again?

323
00:22:31,223 --> 00:22:33,586
Don't mess with my bindaetteok.

324
00:22:34,176 --> 00:22:35,721
All done.

325
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:39,157
Hurry and taste it, Grandma.

326
00:22:41,323 --> 00:22:43,795
Taste it, my foot.

327
00:22:47,323 --> 00:22:49,935
What is this bizarre thing?

328
00:22:50,323 --> 00:22:52,823
Grandma, this is a super trendy...

329
00:22:52,823 --> 00:22:55,808
Dubai-style sweet, chewy,
crispy dessert...

330
00:22:55,808 --> 00:22:57,143
I don't know if you've heard of it.

331
00:22:57,810 --> 00:22:59,657
This is kataifi pastry.

332
00:22:59,657 --> 00:23:02,648
It's eaten in Turkey
and the Middle East...

333
00:23:02,648 --> 00:23:06,252
Whatever it is.

334
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:08,053
Where's the skewer?

335
00:23:08,053 --> 00:23:09,755
Just try it first, Grandma.

336
00:23:09,989 --> 00:23:13,759
If this goes well, it could become
the most famous bindaetteok in Seoul...

337
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:16,295
Before it gets split in two, clean it up.

338
00:23:16,656 --> 00:23:18,470
Later, when this becomes a hit,

339
00:23:18,470 --> 00:23:20,533
you'll be thanking me on your knees.

340
00:23:24,244 --> 00:23:26,572
Maybe it needs cocoa powder on top?

341
00:23:27,930 --> 00:23:29,375
Where's the skewer?

342
00:23:32,978 --> 00:23:35,180
One bottle of makgeolli, please.

343
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:38,617
Makgeolli? Who's going to drink that?

344
00:23:38,797 --> 00:23:39,797
Me.

345
00:23:40,356 --> 00:23:42,523
You can't handle alcohol well.

346
00:23:42,523 --> 00:23:44,462
Your face turns red after just one drink.

347
00:23:44,463 --> 00:23:47,886
What's wrong?
I know you've been stressed lately,

348
00:23:47,886 --> 00:23:50,296
but drinking won't solve anything.

349
00:23:50,296 --> 00:23:52,231
So you won't give it to me?

350
00:23:52,831 --> 00:23:54,232
Then I'll go somewhere else.

351
00:23:55,023 --> 00:23:57,402
No, don't be like that. Sit down.

352
00:23:59,156 --> 00:24:02,140
They say if you get drunk during the day,
you won't recognize your own parents.

353
00:24:02,356 --> 00:24:04,810
It's fine. I don't have parents anyway.

354
00:24:05,576 --> 00:24:08,314
Cho Rong, pull down the shutter.

355
00:24:08,670 --> 00:24:10,549
Put up a sign saying we're closed today.

356
00:24:10,653 --> 00:24:14,386
What? Close the shop?
Are we really not opening today?

357
00:24:14,671 --> 00:24:17,322
You want to go all the way with me today?

358
00:24:17,950 --> 00:24:18,950
What?

359
00:24:19,290 --> 00:24:23,562
You're not the only one...

360
00:24:23,562 --> 00:24:26,064
who's suffering over her kids every day.

361
00:24:26,898 --> 00:24:29,123
I've got my own share too.

362
00:24:29,123 --> 00:24:31,090
Why you too, Grandma?

363
00:24:31,090 --> 00:24:35,394
Fine, let's go all the way today.

364
00:24:36,342 --> 00:24:39,991
Cho Rong, bring two original plates
and a bottle of makgeolli.

365
00:24:39,991 --> 00:24:43,832
The kind that clears you
right to the appendix.

366
00:24:44,456 --> 00:24:45,456
Don't shake it.

367
00:24:50,323 --> 00:24:54,457
I really don't feel like living
these days.

368
00:24:56,223 --> 00:24:58,956
Eun Ae got scammed
and ended up in detention,

369
00:24:59,689 --> 00:25:02,032
Eun Hyeong became unemployed,

370
00:25:03,075 --> 00:25:05,103
and now even Eun Nim, who I trusted...

371
00:25:05,103 --> 00:25:06,872
What? Eun Nim?

372
00:25:06,872 --> 00:25:09,674
What about her? Did she get in trouble?

373
00:25:14,223 --> 00:25:17,349
Why did you follow me here?
We don't even live in the same direction.

374
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:21,223
I just don't feel like going home,
so I'm just killing time.

375
00:25:21,223 --> 00:25:23,522
You're the last person to say that,

376
00:25:23,522 --> 00:25:25,223
living in a huge Gangnam apartment...

377
00:25:25,223 --> 00:25:26,958
with a plastic surgeon husband.

378
00:25:26,958 --> 00:25:30,056
We didn't buy that house.
My parents-in-law did.

379
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:32,418
You wouldn't understand the pressure...

380
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:35,400
unless you've experienced it.

381
00:25:35,703 --> 00:25:37,469
Do you live with your in-laws?

382
00:25:37,623 --> 00:25:40,605
No, they live in the building next door,
but it's practically the same.

383
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:43,041
They're probably at our place even now.

384
00:25:43,722 --> 00:25:46,177
I can't even change out of my uniform...

385
00:25:46,177 --> 00:25:47,773
before having to prepare dinner.

386
00:25:47,773 --> 00:25:50,956
That bad? That sounds really tough.

387
00:25:52,283 --> 00:25:55,316
I actually don't have any in-law stress.

388
00:25:55,956 --> 00:25:59,224
They treat me like their own daughter.

389
00:25:59,690 --> 00:26:01,893
You're lucky.

390
00:26:02,423 --> 00:26:05,764
A capable professor husband
and perfect in-laws.

391
00:26:06,590 --> 00:26:08,066
Perfect? Not really.

392
00:26:09,123 --> 00:26:12,070
As long as there's trust between you,

393
00:26:12,590 --> 00:26:14,957
money isn't really an issue.

394
00:26:16,090 --> 00:26:20,129
Not to brag, but...

395
00:26:21,003 --> 00:26:22,603
I respect my husband.

396
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:26,084
You respect your husband?

397
00:26:28,456 --> 00:26:30,090
I'm so jealous.

398
00:26:30,623 --> 00:26:31,823
Jealous of what?

399
00:26:34,023 --> 00:26:37,529
What should I do?
We're having a party at home today,

400
00:26:37,529 --> 00:26:39,130
and the cake delivery
should be arriving soon.

401
00:26:39,323 --> 00:26:41,066
A party? What kind of party?

402
00:26:41,923 --> 00:26:44,302
My husband...

403
00:26:45,623 --> 00:26:48,239
There's just something to celebrate.
Should we get going?

404
00:26:49,056 --> 00:26:50,642
You really have everything, don't you?

405
00:26:50,909 --> 00:26:51,910
I'll pay for the coffee.

406
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:56,056
Come to the Harvard Campus.

407
00:26:56,056 --> 00:26:58,750
I'll teach you well
and make you top students.

408
00:26:59,017 --> 00:27:01,036
Take a look at this, and this too...

409
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:03,024
- Looks like there's an event.
- Come visit the Harvard Campus.

410
00:27:03,024 --> 00:27:05,190
That man... What a shame.

411
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:07,252
I guess he has no choice
if he wants to make a living.

412
00:27:07,252 --> 00:27:09,224
Friends, make sure to visit
the Harvard campus, okay?

413
00:27:09,224 --> 00:27:10,428
- Yes.
- Take one of these.

414
00:27:11,424 --> 00:27:12,424
Show it to your mom.

415
00:27:13,503 --> 00:27:14,503
What is this?

416
00:27:14,503 --> 00:27:15,504
- Okay?
- Yes.

417
00:27:15,890 --> 00:27:16,890
Bit Na.

418
00:27:18,523 --> 00:27:20,290
- It's Mom.
- What?

419
00:27:20,290 --> 00:27:21,473
Mom.

420
00:27:23,077 --> 00:27:24,077
Bit Na.

421
00:27:30,203 --> 00:27:31,283
Honey...

422
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:34,896
- Seriously...
- What's wrong? Do you know him?

423
00:27:34,896 --> 00:27:37,956
No, I'll see you later.

424
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:40,156
Wait...

425
00:27:48,149 --> 00:27:49,149
Ji Seon.

426
00:28:00,979 --> 00:28:03,982
(Our Happy Days)

427
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:07,390
This isn't a playground
where you can run wild.

428
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:08,390
Manager Seo.

429
00:28:08,390 --> 00:28:11,022
- Why do you keep snooping around my room?
- Sorry?

430
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:14,325
Tell me why you keep snooping around here.

431
00:28:14,325 --> 00:28:15,631
Just wait. No matter what it takes,

432
00:28:15,631 --> 00:28:18,196
I'll uncover every secret in this family.

433
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:20,165
I don't mind you being like that.

434
00:28:20,165 --> 00:28:22,601
Team Manager,
do you like me by any chance?

435
00:28:22,601 --> 00:28:23,601
What?

436
00:28:23,601 --> 00:28:25,403
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
